# EmailJS credentials — get these from https://www.emailjs.com
# 1. Create a free account at emailjs.com
# 2. Add an Email Service (connect your Gmail / Outlook)
# 3. Create an Email Template (see template variables below)
# 4. Copy the IDs below and create a .env file with your real values

VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here

# --- EmailJS Template Variables ---
# The contact form (src/components/home/ProcessAudit.jsx) sends exactly these,
# matched to the current EmailJS dashboard template's body placeholders:
#   {{name}}      — submitter's name
#   {{email}}     — submitter's email (optional)
#   {{phone}}     — phone / WhatsApp number
#   {{title}}     — "Enquiry from {company}", or "Website Enquiry" if no company given
#   {{message}}   — the message text
#   {{reply_to}}  — submitter's email, falls back to phone (set template's "Reply To" to {{reply_to}})
#
# Set "To Email" in your template to: info@macrocoats.in
#
# IMPORTANT: if you edit the template body in the EmailJS dashboard, keep the
# variable names above in sync with the payload built in ProcessAudit.jsx's
# handleSubmit — a mismatch here is a silent failure (fields render blank).
